<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="569" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,534,703]" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,534,559]" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Comments.</emphasis>
This subgenus is characterized by the presence of spinal processes on body in apterae. It is represented by five species worldwide, including a new combination redescribed herein. The Chinese endemic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992" authorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1992" box="[151,734,606,631]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Margituberculatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aphidomorpha" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,359,606,631]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Margituberculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang" box="[372,734,606,631]" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" refString="Zhang, G., Zhong, T. &amp; Zhang, W. (1992) Homoptera: Aphidoidea. In: The Comprehensive Scientific Expedition to the Qinghai-Xizang Plateau, Chinese Academy of Sciences (Ed.), Insects of the Hengduan Mountains Regions. Vol. 1. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 360 - 403." type="book" year="1992">
Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 
<number box="[678,734,607,631]" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan, 1972" authorityName="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan" authorityYear="1972" box="[1003,1112,607,630]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Eoessigia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1112,607,630]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Eoessigia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study (see detailed comments below), 
<taxonomicName authority="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan, 1972" authorityName="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan" authorityYear="1972" box="[367,476,644,667]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Eoessigia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[367,476,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Eoessigia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thereby newly recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[849,920,642,667]" name="China" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">China</collectingCountry>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan, 1972" authorityName="David, Rajasingh &amp; Narayanan" authorityYear="1972" box="[1056,1165,644,667]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Eoessigia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1165,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Eoessigia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly infest 
<taxonomicName box="[1330,1436,643,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="18" pageNumber="569" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
plants and occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[370,457,678,703]" name="Canada" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">Canada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[468,537,678,703]" name="China" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[549,609,678,703]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="569">India</collectingCountry>
, and the Altai Republic.
</paragraph>
